						<persName>Shek, Zeev</persName>
						<note>
							<p>1920–1978</p>
							<p>Born in Olomouc. Active in the Zionist movement, member of Maccabi Hatzair. In 1943 he was deported to the
								Theresienstadt (Terezín) ghetto, where he became one of the Hechalutz leaders. In autumn 1944 he was transported to
								Auschwitz-Birkenau. After the war he became one of the main initiator of the Documentation campaign (Dokumentační
								akce). In 1946 he emigrated to Palestine, where he worked for the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and in the diplomatic
								services. In 1967 Sheck was appointed as the Israeli Ambassador in Vienna. In 1977 he was sent to serve as the Israeli
								Ambassador in Rome, where he has died one year later.</p>
