	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1" facs="EHRI-ET-JMP004_01.jpg"/>
			<p>On <date when="1944-10-20">20.10.1944</date> a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject"
					>labor</term><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">transport</term> was put together
					in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0">Auschwitz</placeName> in camp E. During the medical
				check-up, the examining <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-287" type="subject">doctor</term>removed the following people due to
				physical weakness: <persName ref="#ehri_et_shek_zeev">Zeev Scheck</persName>, <persName
					ref="https://www.holocaust.cz/databaze-obeti/obet/91551-egon-haas/">Egon Haas</persName>, and <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_simonsohn_berthold">Bertl Simonsohn</persName>, because they looked very thin. They were assured that they would be
				sent as <q><foreign xml:lang="de"><distinct type="camp_language">Stubendienst</distinct></foreign></q> to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-496" type="subject">camp</term> for a short time so that they could get
				better and then be sent to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term>. But they
				knew what was going on and <persName ref="#ehri_et_shek_zeev">Zeev</persName> especially tried to get onto the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">transport</term> by showing his muscles and vowing
				that he was used to hard work, that he only appeared thin, but that he was completely healthy. <persName
					ref="https://www.holocaust.cz/databaze-obeti/obet/91551-egon-haas/">Egon Haas</persName> and <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_simonsohn_berthold">Bertl Simonsohn</persName> joined him. They weren’t successful, but were added to the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject">transport</term> in the end only because some people
				were missing.</p>
			<p>It’s interesting that only 4 people survived this <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-518" type="subject"
					>transport</term>, and <persName ref="#ehri_et_shek_zeev">Zeev</persName> and <persName ref="#ehri_et_simonsohn_berthold"
					>Bertl</persName> are among them.</p>

